1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Breyton was born in 1500, her father, John Esq. Breyton, was 38 and her mother, Lady Sybil Milbourne, was 29. She had at least 1 daughter with John Baskerville."},"et":{"1500–":"1500–Surnud","1500–Female":"1500–Surnud","1477–1556":"1477–1556","1528–1593":"1528–1593","1462–1527":"1462–1527","1471–1537":"1471–1537","1556":"1556","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1462":"1462","1593":"1593","1471":"1471","1528":"1528","1527":"1527","1537":"1537","Tilehurst, Berkshire, England":"Tilehurst, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1500–":"1500–Kuollut","1500–Female":"1500–Kuollut","1477–1556":"1477–1556","1528–1593":"1528–1593","1462–1527":"1462–1527","1471–1537":"1471–1537","1556":"1556","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1462":"1462","1593":"1593","1471":"1471","1528":"1528","1527":"1527","1537":"1537","Tilehurst, Berkshire, England":"Tilehurst, Berkshire, England"},"fr":{"1500–":"1500–Décédée","1500–Female":"1500–Décédée","1477–1556":"1477–1556","1528–1593":"1528–1593","1462–1527":"1462–1527","1471–1537":"1471–1537","1556":"1556","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1462":"1462","1593":"1593","1471":"1471","1528":"1528","1527":"1527","1537":"1537","Tilehurst, Berkshire, England":"Tilehurst, Berkshire, Angleterre","lifeS